Create an app.py and requirements.txt file in your cloned repo

#cd model_tutorial
#!touch app.py
#!touch requirements.txt

Log into git
Navigate back to your .ipynb file and input these !git commands (remember to change the email address, username, and password to your account details):

#!git config --global user.email "email@hotmail.com"
#!git config --global user.name "username"
#!git config --global user.password "password"

Push your edited cloned repo folder to Hugging Face

#!git add /notebooks/model_tutorial
#!git commit -m "Add application file"
#!git push

And that should be all you need to do! It’s important to make sure that the current directory you’re working from is the cloned repo folder, before you decided to push anything to your HuggingFace space. You can check which directory you’re currently in using ls - cd repo_path

Create an app.py and requirements.txt file in your cloned repository
Change the current directory on your Paperspace machine to the Hugging Face cloned repository using the cd command, followed by the path to the repository. Use the !touch command to create the app.py and requirements.txt files. Alternatively, you can navigate to the cloned repository in the ‘Files’ tab and manually create the app.py and requirements.txt files by clicking on the ‘New File’ icon and entering the desired file names:

#cd model_tutorial
#!touch app.py
#!touch requirements.txt

Push your Paperspace cloned repository folder to Hugging Face
Before pushing anything to your Hugging Face space, ensure that the current directory you are working from is the cloned repository folder. You can check which directory you’re currently in using ls. If you’re in the correct directory, input these !git commands to upload your Paperspace model to your Hugging Face space:

#!git add /notebooks/model_tutorial
#!git commit -m "Add application file"
#!git push

And that’s it! You’ll need to wait a few minutes for Hugging Face to build the Gradio web app but after that, your model should be live on Hugging Face and available for anyone to use!
